@page "/documentation/week2"

<PageTitle>Week 2 Documentation</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4 mb-5 pb-5">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4">
        <h1 class="fw-bold text-success"><i class="bi bi-journal-check me-2"></i> Week 2 Training: Database Relations & Statistics</h1>
    </div>
    
    <p class="lead text-muted mb-5">This guide covers Foreign Keys, data grids, FusionCharts, and Hyperlink Drilldown reporting.</p>

    <!-- STEP 1: DATABASE RELATIONS -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-dark text-white fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 1: Setup Database (Child Table)
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Create Child Table with Foreign Key</h5>
            <p>We need a <code>Vehicles</code> table linked to <code>EmployeeProfiles</code> via <code>IC_No</code>.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
CREATE TABLE Vehicles (
    VehicleID INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    Owner_IC NVARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    VehicleNo NVARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    Color NVARCHAR(50),
    Brand NVARCHAR(50),
    Model NVARCHAR(50),
    
    -- 1. Create Foreign Key
    CONSTRAINT FK_Vehicles_EmployeeProfiles 
        FOREIGN KEY (Owner_IC) 
        REFERENCES EmployeeProfiles(IC_No)
        ON DELETE CASCADE 
);

-- 2. Index of Each Field (Speeds up searching/drilldowns)
CREATE INDEX IX_Vehicles_OwnerIC ON Vehicles(Owner_IC);
CREATE INDEX IX_Vehicles_Color ON Vehicles(Color);
CREATE INDEX IX_Vehicles_Brand ON Vehicles(Brand);
CREATE INDEX IX_Vehicles_Model ON Vehicles(Model);
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 2: USER INTERFACE (DATA GRID) -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 2: Enhance User Interface (Vehicle Grid)
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Display added vehicle record in data grid</h5>
            <p>In <code>Vehicles.razor</code>, we display the grid utilizing the Foreign Key to pull the Owner Name.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;table class="table table-hover table-bordered"&gt;
    &lt;thead class="table-dark"&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;th&gt;Owner Name&lt;/th&gt;
            &lt;th&gt;Vehicle No&lt;/th&gt;
            &lt;th&gt;Brand&lt;/th&gt;
            &lt;th&gt;Actions&lt;/th&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/thead&gt;
    &lt;tbody&gt;
        @@foreach (var veh in VehiclesList)
        {
            &lt;tr&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;@@veh.OwnerName&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;@@veh.VehicleNo&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;@@veh.Brand&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;
                    &lt!-- 3. Display Detail / 4. Update Form --&gt;
                    &lt;button @@onclick="() =&gt; EditRecord(veh)"&gt;Edit&lt;/button&gt;
                    &lt!-- 5. Delete Record --&gt;
                    &lt;button @@onclick="() =&gt; DeleteRecord(veh)"&gt;Delete&lt;/button&gt;
                &lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;/tr&gt;
        }
    &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 3: STATISTICS & CHARTS -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-info text-white fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 3: Develop User Interface to Display Statistics
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Tabular Report & Graphical Bar Chart (FusionCharts)</h5>
            <p>1. Inject FusionCharts inside <code>App.razor</code>.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;script src="https://cdn.fusioncharts.com/fusioncharts/latest/fusioncharts.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="https://cdn.fusioncharts.com/fusioncharts/latest/themes/fusioncharts.theme.fusion.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            </code></pre>

            <p>2. Create <code>StatCard.razor</code> Repeater Component for Sub-totals & Grand Totals:</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;!-- 1. Tabular Report with Sub-total --&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
    @@foreach(var item in Data) {
        &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;@@item.Name&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;@@item.Count&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
    }
    &lt!-- Grand Total --&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;GRAND TOTAL:&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;@@Data.Sum(x =&gt; x.Count)&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;!-- 2. Graphical Bar Chart Report --&gt;
&lt;div id="@@ChartId"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 4: DRILLDOWN REPORTS -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-warning text-dark fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 4: Develop Drilldown Sub-report User Interface
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Hyperlink Approaches (Pop-up vs Redirect)</h5>
            
            <p><strong>1. Open Sub-report using Redirect (URL Query params)</strong></p>
            <p>Pass the filter via URL: <code>/users?searchGender=Male</code>. The target page uses <code>[SupplyParameterFromQuery]</code>.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;!-- 1. Hyperlink on Sub-Total --&gt;
&lt;a href="/users?searchGender=@@item.Name"&gt;@@item.Count&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;!-- Target Page captures it --&gt;
@@code {
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? searchGender { get; set; }
    
    protected override async Task OnParametersSetAsync() {
        // Loads specific data on URL change
        await LoadData(searchGender); 
    }
}
            </code></pre>

            <p><strong>2. Open Sub-report using Pop-up (Inline Modal)</strong></p>
            <p>Uses an <code>EventCallback</code> to open a hidden Bootstrap Modal containing the sub-report table.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;!-- Pass the Click Event --&gt;
&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" @@onclick="() =&gt; OpenModal(item.Name)"&gt;@@item.Count&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;!-- 3. Drilldown Sub-report Pop-up --&gt;
@@if (isModalOpen) {
    &lt;div class="modal fade show d-block"&gt;
        &lt;!-- Load Vehicle Sub-Report Data Grid Here --&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
}
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
